    style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>The analysis deep dives into each header, and which values are being sent, including misconfigured / invalid variations.  The author ends with this conclusion:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>There’s a lot that we can do with these security headers - but based on the data in the HTTP Archive it’s pretty clear that they are not being used enough and sometimes are being used incorrectly.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>For additional reading, take a look at:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"../2018-04-27-content-security-policy-http-header-braindump\">Content-Security-Policy HTTP Header Braindump</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"../2018-02-07-referrer-policy-http-header\">Referrer-Policy HTTP header</a></li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"title":"Adoption of HTTP Security Headers on the Web","date":"March 06, 2018","tags":["http","security"]}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/2018-03-06-adoption-of-http-security-headers-on-the-web","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/2018-02-09-marking-http-pages-as-not-secure"},"frontmatter":{"tags":["http","webdev","security"]}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/2018-03-08-access-logs-from-aws-services"},"frontmatter":{"tags":["aws","http","monitoring"]}}}}}